value.value: The line that separates the dorsal and lateral axillar surfaces.
The area that is heavily sclerotized and located proximally on the posterior wing margin.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the axillary sclerites.
The sclerite that is located on the axillary region and articulates with one of the thoracic wing processes.
The area that is located laterally on the mesoscutellum and is limited anteriorly by the scutoscutellar suture and medially by the axillular line.
The axillular line that is a carina.
The row of setae that extends along the median margin of axillula.
The area that is oblong and differs from surrounding areas in coloration, surface sculpture and setae.
The process that is linear and wider proximally than distally.
The area that connects the parosicculi.
The row of impressions that extends along the anterior margin of an abdominal tergum or a sternum.
The anatomical cluster that is part of the gonostyle/volsella complex and is composed of the sclerites that are proximal to the harpe.

label.value: basal transverse carina of third abdominal tergite

value.value: The carina that extends along the proximal margin of the third abdominal tergite.
The wing vein that is basally located on the fore wing and connects or nearly connects the submarginal vein and the medial plus cubital veins.
The sclerite that is located on the dorsal margin of the pectus of pterothoracic segment anteriorly of the pleural wing articulation.
The ridge that is located proximally and submarginally in the coxa.
The sulcus that corresponds to the basicosta.
The area that is located on the coxa proximal to the basicostal suture.
The area that is located anteriorly of the site of origin of the furca.
The notch that is located proximally on the median surface of the probasitarsus.
The tarsomere that is the proximal most annulus of the tarsus, connected proximally with the tibia and distally with the second tarsomere via membranous conjunctivae.
The area that is the proximal part of the gonossiculus and corresponds to the site of insertion of medial penisvalvo-gonossiculal muscle.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of small sclerites and is located proximally on the first valvulae.
The area that is located distally on the mandible.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the whole organism but which excludes the antennae, legs and wings.
The segment that is the part of the body.
The anatomical region of the wing vein that is less melanized and more flexible than surrounding anatomical wing vein regions and corresponds to the intersection of the wing vein with a flexion line.
The broadened portion of the lateral oviduct is enlarged and contains virus particles (characterized by bluish autofluorescence).

The sclerite that is articulated with the cranium at the cranio-cardinal articulation, is connected to the stipes distolaterally via the stipitocardinal hinge and receives the site of attachment of the occipito-cardinal muscle.
The process that is elongate and external.
The conjunctiva that is folded and located on the anterior margin of the metanotum and covered (at least partially) with setae.
The sense organ that located apicolaterally on one of the apicalmost abdominal terga and attaches to a large nerve cord.
The apodeme that is located posteriorly of and continuous with the cervical prominence and corresponds to the site of insertion of laterocervical muscles.
The articular process that is located on the anterior margin of the propleuron and bears the cranial condyle of the propleuron.
The area that is located medially on the pronotum and is delimited laterally by the epomial carina.
The row of stout spines that is located along the anterior edge of the protibia.
The seta that is located on a process.
The anatomical space that is delimited dorsally by the wall of the metascutellum, anteriorly and posteriorly by the bifurcated internal metanotal ridge.
The area that is located ventrally in between the eye and the oral foramen.
The anatomical space that is the anteriormost part of the alimentary canal and is delimited proximally by the proximomedian margin of the sitophore and distally by the functional mouth.
The ridge that extends along the margin of the compound eye and corresponds to the ocular suture.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of apical flagellomeres bearing multiporous plates in female organism.
The wing fold that is located on the fore wing, parallels the anal vein, and extends to the claval notch on the wing margin.
The wing region that is posterior to the claval furrow and anterior to the jugal fold.
The setiferous patch that is used to clean anatomical structures.
The rim that extends along the distal margin of the clypeus.
The process that is located medially on the clypeus.
The line that extends from the anterior tentorial pit to the cranial margin and separates the clypeus laterally from the pleurostoma.
The area that corresponds to the site of origin of the clypeo-epipharyngeal muscle.
The glandula mucosa that secretes an adhesive substance used to fasten the eggs to a support.
